To fix the SQL Injection vulnerability in the given Java code snippet, you should use PreparedStatement instead of concatenating user input directly into the SQL query. PreparedStatements in Java provide a way to create parameterized queries that prevent SQL Injection attacks by separating the SQL code from the user input.

Here's how you can fix the code snippet:

